snippet.textDisplay: This Lakers unit looks great, doesn't it? Against a ninth-seeded team featuring a budding rookie with unbroken promises, who are a far cry from possibly the first two rounds, the Western Conference and NBA Finals. Yet, still, the bandwagoners, casual fans and most of all, the LeBronites are drowning in their own fantasies. But that's fine and dandy. Zion Lateef Williamson haven't yet gotten his feet wet. The latter will get his rewards, one day, but not now. Perhaps next season, or some time afterwards. LeBron Raymone James, Sr. has gotten another triple-double without Anthony Marshon Davis, Jr. However, that situation won't continue, if the latter is out for long stretches. As for the rest of this Lakers unit, the worst is yet to come. Their second bench is still weak, and it will be documented during the playoffs. I reiterate...if this particular Lakers unit get to the 2020 NBA Finals, which I highly doubted, they will get swept, indefinitely. Ciao!
